# TypeDB Query Standards

## Purpose
Keep TypeDB schema and query work explicit, semantically correct, and maintainable.

## Requirements
- preserve clear distinction between entities, relations, and attributes
- model domain meaning explicitly rather than overloading a relation
- keep query intent readable and easy to review
- separate schema evolution from retrieval/query changes when possible
- prefer additive schema evolution before destructive changes
- make assumptions about uniqueness, cardinality, and ownership explicit
- keep application result-mapping logic separate from raw query logic
- avoid hidden semantic shortcuts that make future schema evolution harder
- document migration implications when changing types or attributes

## Apply When
- designing or modifying TypeDB schema
- writing or debugging queries
- mapping TypeDB results into application types
